<HEADLINE> Volkswagen to Resume Car Production in Sarajevo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Germany's largest carmaker Volkswagen
AG announced Tuesday that it would resume car production at a
plant in the Bosnian capital city of Sarajevo where it was forced
to leave during the Bosnian civil war.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed Tuesday by Volkswagen and its Bosnian
partner company Unis Holding, the Volkswagen plant in Sarajevo is
due to resume production from this month with an initial output of
5,000 to 10,000 Skoda Felicia vehicles a year.
</P>
<P>
The Volkswagen plant in Sarajevo was badly damaged during the
war by Serb forces. Volkswagen said it planned to put an
investment of 48 million marks (26.48 million U.S. dollars) in the
new venture which the company will hold a 58 percent stake while
Unis Holding will have 42 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
