<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Croatia not to be Under-estimated: Deschamps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CLAIREFONTAINE, France, July 7 (Xinhua) -- France's Didier
Deschamps said on Tuesday that France should not under-estimate their
World Cup semifinal opponents Croatia although the latter has not been
regarded as favorite.
</P>
<P>
"We are very proud to have reached the semi-final, but we must make
sure we don't get carried away," he said in the team's training base
in Clairefontaine south-west of Paris.
</P>
<P>
"We still remember only too well the European Championship, where
we took it for granted that we would reach the final even before our
semi-final match against the Czechs. We learn from our mistakes."
</P>
<P>
The Juventus midfielder said he would have to keep the situation
under control in Wednesday's game and "not make any stupid mistakes".
</P>
<P>
But Deschamps, who received a yellow card in the quarter-final
against Italy, said "that doesn't mean that I will be any less
aggressive."
</P>
<P>
He added, "we will have to concentrate hard in defence. I think it
is individual talent that will decide the match."
</P>
<P>
He said he knew Croatia's coach Miroslav Blazevic from his early
days at FC Nantes in the French league.
</P>
<P>
"He's an intelligent, charming and crafty man. He knows how to get
the best out of his players as he has great confidence in himself, and
his self-belief is infectious."
</P>
<P>
France will meet Croatia at the new Stade de France in Saint-Denis
outside Paris on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
