<HEADLINE> Kuwait's Exports up 73 Percent in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait's exports, mainly to
the Gulf Arab countries, reached 21.1 million U.S. dollars in May,
an increase of 73 percent over April, said an official report
released Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report issued by Kuwait's Ministry of Trade and Industry
said that Kuwait's exports to Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC)
member states reached 14.2 million dollars, which accounted for
some 68 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the share of its exports to other Arab and non-Arab
countries stood at about 32 percent.
</P>
<P>
The report said Saudi Arabia is the biggest importer of Kuwaiti
goods in the GCC, absorbing 58 percent of Kuwaiti exports. Saudi
Arabia is followed by the United Arab Emirates, 19 percent and
Qatar, 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait's exports mainly included foodstuff, soft-drinks,
soybean oil, processed meat, dairy, animal fat and juice, the
report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
