percent increase on first half registrations in 1997, which
totaled 1,054,715.
</P>
<P>
In June, British-made cars took a 34.5 percent market share,
while in the year to date they had a 33 percent market share.
</P>
<P>
June's commercial vehicle registrations totaled 25,171 units, a
27 percent increase on the June 1997 figure of 19,816.
</P>
<P>
Truck registrations reached 4,520 units, up 26.7 percent on
June 1997's figure of 3,567.
</P>
<P>
Total commercial vehicle registration in the first six months
of 1998 reached 149,592, up 12.9 percent on the same time last
year.
</P>
<P>
Roger King, SMMT acting chief executive, said, "This is a very
good result and is the direct consequence of manufacturers
