<HEADLINE> Africa's Museums Organization to Be Set Up in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Coordination Program of African
Museums will become a regional professional organization in 1999,
uniting all cultural and intellectual groups in the continent.
</P>
<P>
Valery Chieze who is in charge of the coordination program
under the International Commission of Museums revealed this
during her trip to Angola earlier this month, the Angolan News
Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chieze also attended the regional convention on museum
management in central Africa.
</P>
<P>
The main purpose of the meeting was to establish a proper
mechanism for the Coordination Program of African Museums and
make it a regional professional organization so as to better
preserve the museums and promote the African culture.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that a meeting will be held in Lome later in
1998 to work out a new plan for the establishment of such an
organization.
</P>
<P>
Meetings will also be held in Angola, Zambia and the
Democratic Republic of Congo to discuss and resolve issues
concerning languages, history and administration in the process
of setting up the pan-African museum association.
</P>
<P>
Then, a convention will be called in Zambia in 1999 to
officially proclaim the establishment of the professional
organization of museums in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The major function of the Coordination Program of African
Museums is to define the African cultural policy, design cultural
plans and gather together the professionals of museums from
different countries in a bid to preserve the African heritage.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
