<HEADLINE> Resolution Upgrading PLO's Status at U.N. Adopted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The General Assembly of the
United Nations Tuesday adopted a resolution which upgraded the
status of the Palestinian U.N. observer delegation.
</P>
<P>
The resolution was adopted with 124 votes for, four against and
10 abstentions. The United States, Israel, Micronesia and the
Marshall Islands voted against the resolution.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the resolution, the Palestinian delegation
will now be able to co-sponsor resolutions on Palestinian and
Middle East issues, take part in the assembly's general debate,
speak on non-Middle East issues at assembly meetings immediately
after the last inscribed member states, exercise a right of reply,
raise points of order at meetings on Palestinian and Middle East
issues, and be seated in the assembly hall after non-member states
Switzerland and the Holy See and before other observers.
</P>
<P>
Under the resolution, the Palestinian delegation will still not
have the right to vote or to submit candidates for various U.N.
posts and offices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
