<HEADLINE> Gaddafi's Surgery Proved Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The surgery for the broken left femur
of Libyan leader Moammar Gaddafi, conducted by Libyan surgeons
Monday evening, has proved successful.
</P>
<P>
According to the Libyan News Agency Tuesday, the operation was
performed after Gaddafi's meeting with missions of Muslim
countries to the religious ceremony marking the birthday of
Islamic Prophet Mohammed.
</P>
<P>
Gaddafi had a broken femur on Monday while practicing routine
sports exercises, the agency said, with giving details.
</P>
<P>
Presidents of Senegal, Sierra Leone, Niger, Chad, Gambia and
Mali as well as missions from other Muslim countries attended the
ceremony Monday evening in Baidaa town, east Libyan capital
Tripoli. 
</P>
