<HEADLINE> Uganda Urged to Intensify Anti-Drug Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A United Nations anti-drug
official has urged Uganda to form a drug coordinating committee
to intensify the country's fight against drug abuse.
</P>
<P>
Muki Daniel, assistant representative of the United Nations
Drug Control Program for East and Southern Africa, made the
appeal when addressing a cross section of members of the Uganda
Broadcasters Forum (UBROF) here Tuesday afternoon, the Uganda
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Daniel said the committee should have representatives to
promote drug abuse control.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of her visit to Uganda is to talk to different
actors and donors about the need to step up measures against drug
abuse in the east African country, she added.
</P>
<P>
The UBROF President, Samuel Muwanguzi, thanked the U.N. drug
control program for extending financial assistance to the Forum.
</P>
<P>
He said the U.N. organization's help has enabled UBROF to open
a sensitization workshop on the hazards of drug abuse and make an
anti-drug abuse television program starting next month.
</P>
<P>
Muwanguzi revealed that his forum has designed a program to
sensitize all students in Uganda about drug abuse and promised to
continue the efforts in this direction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
