<DOCNO> XIE19980708.0067 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Parliament Approves 1998/99 Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian parliament, the
House of People's Representatives, approved Tuesday the 11.116
billion Birr (about 1.57 billion U.S. Dollars) budget for 1998/99
financial year, 6.3 percent more than the 1997/98 financial year
which ended Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, 4.05 billion Birr (577
million Dollars) of the budget is allocated for the regular
expenditure, 2.91 billion Birr (409 million Dollars) for capital
expenditure, and the remaining for subsidy appropriation to
regional states.
</P>
<P>
The regular expenditure is 7.8 percent more than the 3.75
billion Birr of previous year, while the capital expenditure is
4.7 percent decrease from the 3.05 billion Birr of previous year.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, 40.7 percent of the budget is
obtained from government treasury while foreign aid and loan
account to 22.2 percent and 37.1 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Among the capital expenditure, 49.8 percent of the budget is
earmarked for road construction, 6.9 percent for education, 10.1
percent for agriculture and 13.7 percent for transport and
communications.  
</P>
</TEXT>
