<HEADLINE> France Lacks Finishing Power: Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CLAIREFONTAINE, France, July 7 (Xinhua) -- French coach Aime
Jacquet said on Tuesday that the lack of finishing power remained the
main problem for his team.
</P>
<P>
"The main problem with France is with the finishing," said Jacquet,
whose side will play Croatia in the World Cup semifinal in Paris on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He added: "It is up to the other players to creat better openings
for the attackers, if they could find the composure they need."
</P>
<P>
Jacquet said: "The three biggest threats awaiting the French team
tomorrow are: a lack of concentration, not succeeding in playing our
own game, and losing our lucidity and confidence in our abilities."
</P>
<P>
But the coach blamed the press for "deceiving" the public, saying
"from what they said one would think that France didn't have a team or
a coach."
</P>
<P>
He added: "We are all honored by the fervor that is surrounding us.
We are all very proud to reach the semifinals. I hope that tomorrow
night the last two years of careful preparations will pay their
dividents." 
</P>
</TEXT>
