<HEADLINE> Taiwan Straits Association Vice-President Talks With Journalists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Tang Shubei, the vice-president of
the Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits, in a
meeting with journalists here this afternoon, said that problems
between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits should be solved by
people on both sides and that this is the Chinese government's
principle.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that the two sides have reached a common
understanding on political negotiations which, if it is really
implemented, could mean a more promising future, and he expressed
the hope that people on both sides can seize the opportunity to
promote relations. His organization, ARATS, is willing to hold
discussions with Taiwanese compatriots, whether they agree with
the reunification cause or not, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that ARATS recently received a formal letter from the
Taiwan Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF) proposing a visit by Koo
Chen-fu, its chairman, to the mainland in the autumn. According to
Tang, his organization replied that they hope Mr Koo can visit in
mid-September or mid-October.
</P>
<P>
Tang pointed out that, although in recent speeches some
prominent Taiwanese indicated that they do not reject political
negotiations, the letter from SEF did not mention this matter.
</P>
<P>
He said that since the 'one country, two systems' principle has
been successful in Hong Kong and has gotten praise from around the
globe, it could also be useful in Taiwan, and that, under the 'One
China' principle, his organization is willing to discuss any issue
as long as it facilitates the peaceful reunification of China.
</P>
<P>
In a separate matter, Tang said that his organization has given
the four Taiwanese spies who were arrested letters from their
families and other necessary items that were sent, and has
forwarded their replies to their families, which is a humanitarian
service that ARATS is ready and willing to provide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
