<HEADLINE> French Experts in Iraq to Check Chemical Missile Allegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Three French experts have arrived in
Baghdad to investigate allegations that Iraq equipped its missile
heads with VX gas chemical weapons during the 1991 Gulf War,
French Foreign Ministry assistant spokesman Yves Doutriaux said on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The experts will assist in taking samples of missile heads for
a technical valuation in a French laboratory from the end of July
till the end of August at the request of the United Nations
special commission in Iraq (UNSCOM), said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He said that the operation was not a counter-checking of the
missile heads following earlier analysis by U.S. experts.
</P>
<P>
Three Swiss experts specializing in atomic and chemical weapons
will also go to Iraq to join the operation, announced the Swiss
Foreign Ministry the same day. 
</P>
