<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak Opposition Leaders Express Concern Over Law, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Senior leaders of the Karachi
Office of the Opposition Pakistan People's Party (PPP) have
expressed their concern over the deteriorating law and order
situation in Karachi, the southern port city.
</P>
<P>
President and Secretary General of the PPP Karachi Office Taj
Haider and Haji Muzaffar Shujra issued a joint statement Wednesday
criticizing the coalition government in Sindh province for its
failure to maintain law and order.
</P>
<P>
They said that PPP Karachi Office has constantly been demanding
that infiltration of illegal arms into the city be stopped and
that the lives and properties of the innocent citizens be
protected.
</P>
<P>
They said that the PPP believes in non-violent politics but
would not allow its peaceful and innocent workers to become
victims of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Karachi, Pakistan's industrial and commercial center, has been
hit hard by unchecked violence. More than 160 people are reported
to have been killed since June 1 this year. 
</P>
