<HEADLINE> Half A Million People Visit China's New Commodity Market Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A website belonging to China's
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) on the
Internet was visited 60,000 times on July 1, the first day it
opened.
</P>
<P>
There were 114,000 visits to the "China Market" site on
Tuesday, Ministry officials reported today. According to Xing Wei,
director of MOFTEC's China International Electronic Commerce
Center (CIECC), in the past week it was visited 562,000 times by
people from the United States, Canada, Japan, and dozens of other
countries and some regions.
</P>
<P>
"China Market" can be reached at http://www.chinamarket.com.cn
and MOFTEC can be reached at its official web site
http://www.moftec.gov.cn.
</P>
<P>
Xing Wei explains that "China market" has 6 major product
categories: electronics and machinery; textiles; light industry
and crafts; foodstuffs, native produce, and animal by-products;
hardware, minerals, and chemicals; and medicine and nutritional
products.
</P>
<P>
CIECC's Ma Yun says that businesses have been active on the
website but no deals are known to have been concluded so far.
</P>
<P>
The Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Shi
Guangsheng says that he believes that the website is a solid step
by China to move into the age of e-commerce. The United Nations'
International Telecommunication Union estimates that the world
could do 50 billion U.S. dollars worth of e-commerce this year,
and 300 billion by the year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
