<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Slide in Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Share Prices continued to slide
on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index (STII) lost 7.40 points to close at 1,107.78
points.
</P>
<P>
Total Turnover dropped to 81.46 million shares, valued at
122.39 million Singapore dollars (71.70 million U.S. dollars).
Losers led gainers by 227 to 46 while 318 stocks remained
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
MBF land was the most active stock which closed on a turnover
of 8.00 million units. M Res had 3.31 million counters done. RHB
Cap was next with 3.27 million shares changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 topped the gainers of the day as it increased by 60
cents to 21.10 Singapore dollars. Venture gained 14 cents to
finish at 3.76 Singapore dollars. SP Ld rose by 12 cents to end at
3.34 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, DBS was the biggest loser as it lost 25 cents
to finish at 7.00 Singapore dollars. SIA F was down 25 cents to
end at 8.40 Singapore dollars. CityDev was down 16 cents to close
at 2.04 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said shares ended lower as fears of a recession weighed
on the market.
</P>
<P>
They also said that the much anticipated speech by Japanese
Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto announcing permanent income tax
cuts failed to spur last minutes buying.
</P>
<P>
The market was disappointed that he did not include any details
of the size of nature of the cuts.  
</P>
