<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 50 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the Bombay
Stock Exchange (BSE) market Wednesday closed at 3,245.88 points as
against last close of 3,195.94, netting a gain of 49.94 points.
</P>
<P>
The national index advanced further by 21.04 points to 1,428.45
from previous close of 1,407.41.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the u.s. dollar index were quoted remarkably up
at 325.56 points and 127.21 points compared with Tuesday's close
of 321.14 and 125.92 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities sustained their upward march aiding the sensitive
index to break 3,240 resistance on the stock market Wednesday in
the wake of fresh buying by bulls as well as bears along with
selective support from institutional investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
