<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Output Maintains Steady Growth in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- China's national industrial value
grew by 176 billion yuan this June, a 7.9 percent increase over
the same month last year, maintaining the same growth rate as the
previous month, according to the State Statistics Bureau (SSB).
</P>
<P>
A report issued by the SSB said that state-owned and
state-holding industries experienced an added value of 96.7
billion yuan, up 2.7 percent from the same month last year;
collectively owned industries finished with an added value of 45.5
billion yuan, up 6.4 percent; shareholding, foreign-funded and
other types of industries had an added value of 529 billion yuan,
up 12 percent.
</P>
<P>
In June, light industry had an added value of 77.9 billion
yuan, increasing 7.6 percent over the same month last year;and
heavy industry had an added value of 98.1 billion yuan, an
increase of 8.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same month last year, the growth rates of
color TV sets, computers, steel, flat glass, chemical fertilizers
and other major industrial products ranged between eight percent
and 16 percent, and sales of industrial products remained steady.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman with the SSB said that current industrial
production has been negatively affected by such factors as market
demand restrictions, slow export growth and efficiency
decline. Further efforts should be made by various departments and
localities to continue steady industrial growth, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
