<HEADLINE> International Economic and Trade Fair In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The '98 Qingdao International
Economic and Trade Fair opened in east China's port city of
Qingdao today, with more than 5,000 Chinese and foreign
businessmen attending the event.
</P>
<P>
The fair has 560 booths displaying 2,000 types of
commodities. Shandong Province, where Qingdao is located, is
looking for 25.2 billion US dollars worth of investment for 1,340
projects in automobiles, electronics, machinery, port building,
chemical industry, and building materials.
</P>
<P>
The fair is expected to have 1.7 billion US dollar worth of
import and export contract, or 600 million US dollars more than
for the last fair.
</P>
<P>
It will also have seminars on key projects. The fair will run
through July 13. 
</P>
