<HEADLINE> Qatar Receives French-made Mirage 2000 Aircraft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Qatari armed forces received
an unspecified number of French-made Mirage 5/2000 aircraft in
capital Doha Wednesday, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The reports said that the warplanes, whose number was not
revealed, were the third batch Qatar has purchased from France to
strengthen its defense capability.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony was held for the occasion, and the new aircraft,
flown by Qatari pilots, performed in the skies to display their
high combativeness.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the first batch of Mirages arrived in Qatar
last December, and the second in April.
</P>
<P>
Over 70 percent of the equipment of the Qatari armed forces are
French-made, the reports added. 
