<HEADLINE> Italian Club Willing to Sign Japanese Player </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Italian club Perugia announced that
they have offered a contract to Japanese player Hidetoshi Nakata.
</P>
<P>
Perugia's president Alessandro Gaucci said that he had reached a
gentleman's agreement with Nakata after two months of negotiations
with Nakata's J-League club Bellmare Hiratsuka.
</P>
<P>
Gucci said he was preparing to go to Japan next week with
another official to sign a five-year contract with the 21-year-old
Japanese playmaker who made a good impression in the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
If Nakata joins Perugia, he would become the second Japanese
player to play in the Italian league Serie A after Kazuyoshi Miura,
who played for Genoa in 1994-1995 season. 
</P>
