<HEADLINE> Overpass Collapse in Southwestern China Injures Two Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A 30-m section of an overpass that
was being built in Kunming, the capital of China's Yunnan
Province, collapsed early this morning, slightly injuring two
workers and causing more than 100,000 yuan (about 12,000 US
dollars) in damage.
</P>
