<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Symposium Promotes Beijing, Hong Kong Trade Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- More than 200 business people and
experts from Hong Kong and Beijing gathered here today to attend a
symposium on trade and service cooperation between the two places.
</P>
<P>
At the symposium, the participants discussed and exchanged
views on the development of the public-service industry, the
management of tourism and hotels, the information industry and
infrastructure construction and real estate management in the two
metropolitan cities.
</P>
<P>
According to Yi Xiqun, director of the Beijing Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation Commission, Beijing has focused on
developing the service industry in recent years. The revenue from
the service industry last year accounted for 53.8 percent of the
city's gross domestic product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
Last year, Beijing earned 3.88 billion U.S. dollars from
foreign trade, but its hard currency income from non-trade sectors
reached 5.12 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Yi said Beijing has great potential to tap its service industry
and has a lot to learn from Hong Kong in this respect. He said he
hoped the symposium would increase exchange and cooperation
between the two places.
</P>
<P>
The symposium was sponsored by Beijing Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation Commission and the Hong Kong Trade and
Development Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
