<HEADLINE> China's Major Bank Develops Agent Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial Bank
of China (ICBC) has reported success in developing its agent
business for the country's young policy banks, a bank official
said.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC, China's largest bank, had now functioned as agents
for 584 projects financed by the State Development Bank (SDB), the
country's largest policy bank, founded in 1994 to finance the
construction of major national projects. The ICBC has acted as
agents in business transactions valued at 84.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC has also maintained excellent business relations with
the Export and Import Bank of China (EximBank), a policy-oriented
bank set up in 1994 to finance China's exports of capital goods
such as machinery, electronics and other equipment. So far,
EximBank has entrusted ICBC to act as agents for 30 export
projects with a total value of 3.3 billion yuan, about
one-third of EximBank's total business entrusted to other banks.
</P>
<P>
"Working as agents for the policy banks has both solved the
policy banks' problem of lacking operational subsidiaries and
settlement means and enabled us to expand our own business," an
ICBC official said.
</P>
<P>
ICBC has a wide subsidiary network across China and in many
large cities around the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
