<HEADLINE> Reasons Behind Booming Restaurant Business in Nanjing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Extravagance and waste at public
expense represent the two major factors contributing to the
booming restaurant sector in Nanjing, capital of Jiangsu Province,
according to today's edition of Guangming Daily.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing, a city with three million urban residents and a
transient population of 500,000 workers, has over 15,000
restaurants, or one for every 240 people.
</P>
<P>
The city's restaurants, including the most expensive, are
thriving in spite of their large number in the city.
</P>
<P>
For example, the Meiyuan Restaurant in the Jinling Hotel, the
city's only five-star hotel, generates a daily turnover of 40,000
yuan (4,819 US dollars), with the Seafood Restaurant on the
Jianianhua Club earning 120,000 yuan daily.
</P>
<P>
Reporters visited several restaurants and found that many
customers were discussing business over dinner, with some 80
percent paying for meals with either credit cards or checks.
</P>
<P>
They also found extensive waste in terms of uneaten food and
partially filled drink containers, including many expensive items.
</P>
<P>
The article points out that Nanjing is not only one of the
nation's fastest growing areas, but is also home to many
enterprises with financial problems and has a huge number of
laid-off workers. "The city's economic development calls for
practicing thrift. Please drink less alcohol, and work more,"
according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
