<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Opens Anti-Drug Hot Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 8 (Xinhua) -- China's southern city of
Guangzhou today opened its first anti-drug hot line to offer help
to young drug addicts.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the Guangzhou city committee of the Communist
Youth League of China, the hot line mainly aims to promote the
state policy on drug control, and give instructions on drug
rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
The hot line has drawn the enthusiastic participation of the
majority of people. Nearly 30 young volunteers from local colleges
and medical institutions have been trained as operators.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that Guangzhou has registered 30,000
drug addicts, 80 percent of whom are 18-to-35 years old. Local
officials have set up 21 rehabilitation centers in an attempt to
curb the spread of drug use.  
