<HEADLINE> Rumors About Earthquakes in Tehran Denied </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Geophysics Institute of Tehran
University Wednesday categorically denied a prediction that
earthquakes will hit the capital in the coming two weeks.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the institute rejected the prediction by
a Slovak that earthquakes will take place in Tehran at 02:32 local
time on July 10 (2302 July 9 GMT) and at 09:15 (0545 GMT) on July
13.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the prediction was reported "without
offering any scientific methods," terming it as void of any
scientific validity.
</P>
<P>
Due to the complexity of factors behind earthquakes, no
reliable scientific body has been able to predict the precise
location and time of a quake, the statement stressed.
</P>
<P>
In recent days, Tehran citizens have rushed to buy daily
necessities for fear of possible earthquakes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
