<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed above
62 U.S. cents for the first time in more than a week Wednesday as
financial markets held their breath in anticipation of market
friendly news from Japan.
</P>
<P>
John Reedyk, head of foreign exchange sales with ANZ bank, said
the local currency had a reasonably quiet session ahead of a
speech by Japan's Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto.
</P>
