from 61.62 U.S. cents Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
After the local close, Hashimoto said his government would
bring in permanent income tax cuts next year, according to Kyodo
News.
</P>
<P>
Much of the upward movement in the Australian dollar was etched
out in overnight offshore dealings, with U.S. institutions adding
some flavor.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended unchanged at 86.15 Japanese yen,
and at 1.1281 German marks from 1.1177 marks Tuesday. 
