<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Expresses Condolences on Abiola's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim, secretary
general of the Organization of African Unity (OAU), issued a
statement Wednesday, expressing condolences on "the sudden and
most untimely death" of Chief M.K. Abiola of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued here by the OAU
information division, Salim said "It is a great and irreplaceable
loss to his family and a serious setback to the Nigerian people"
and "it is particularly tragic that the death of this prominent
Nigerian leader has come at a time when his release to freedom
was imminent."
</P>
<P>
"Chief Abiola commanded the respect and support of millions of
Nigerians, cutting across ethnic, religious and other boundaries,
both for his political leadership and his philanthropic
activities," Salim said, adding that "His concern and activities
were not confined to Nigeria. He used his influence and
resources to support many legitimate African causes."
</P>
<P>
"We in the OAU," Salim said, "will always remember him for his
outstanding and dedicated leadership for the cause of reparations
for which he chaired the group of eminent persons."
</P>
<P>
Salim noted that in the last few years, Chief Abiola has come
to be an important symbol of the pro-democracy movement in
Nigeria. The most fitting tribute therefore that can be given to
him is to ensure that democratic government is restored in
Nigeria as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
"Given the encouraging and positive steps that have been
recently taken by the present government under the leadership of
the head of state, General Abdulsalam Abubakar, I am confident
that the current leadership of Nigeria is aware of the challenge
that lies ahead and will live up to the aspirations of the
Nigerian people," Salim added.
</P>
<P>
He also appealed to the Nigerian government to release all the
remaining political prisoners.
</P>
<P>
Abiola died of a heart attack Tuesday afternoon at 4 p.m.
local time at the age of 60. 
</P>
</TEXT>
