<HEADLINE> Malaysian, Australian Securities Bodies to Cooperate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's Securities
Commission (SC) and Australian Securities and Investments
Commission (ASIC) are to establish a framework for assistance and
mutual cooperation, the SC said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The two parties have signed a memorandum of understanding (MOU)
to facilitate the exchange of information to enforce and ensure
compliance with the securities and futures laws of the respective
countries, it said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The SC hoped the cooperation would help increase investor
protection and further promote the integrity of the securities,
futures and options markets of Malaysia and Australia.
</P>
<P>
SC Chairman Munir Majid said the MOU reflected the shared
belief of the two commissions in the urgent need for continued
strengthening of the oversight of the securities and futures
market internationally in the face of globalization and
liberalization. 
</P>
