<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Total Reserves Increase: Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 8 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's total gold and
foreign reserves stood at 33.38 billion Rand (5.56 billion U.S.
Dollars) in late June, up 527.8 million Rand (88 million Dollars)
on the May figure, the Reserve Ban its monthly statement of assets and liabiliti
es, the South
African Reserve Bank said the gold reserves of the country rose
766.8 million Rand (127.8 million U.S. Dollars) to 6.34 billion
Rand (1.06 billion U.S. Dollars) during the month.
</P>
<P>
Foreign assets fell 239 million Rand (40 million U.S. Dollars)
to 27.05 billion Rand (4.5 billion U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Government loans and advances increased 20.48 million Rand
(3.4 million U.S. Dollars) to 626.45 million Rand (104.2 million
U.S. Dollars), the bank said.
</P>
<P>
Utilization of cash reserves and government securities rose by
1.58 billion Rand (263 million U.S. Dollars) and 7.64 million
Rand (1.27 million U.S. Dollars) to 1.99 billion Rand (332
million U.S. Dollars) and 6.17 billion Rand (1.03 billion U.S.
Dollars) respectively.
</P>
<P>
Gold holdings rose from 4,057,593 to 4,077,203 fine ounces.
The Rand price of gold per fine ounce increased 181.47 Rand to
1554.13 Rand.
</P>
<P>
On the liabilities side, notes and coins in circulation rose
451 million Rand (75.2 million U.S. Dollars) to peg at 23.3
billion Rand (3.88 billion U.S. Dollars). 
</P>
