<HEADLINE> Yantai Continues to Develop Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Yantai, a port city in east China's
Shandong Province, recorded an import-export value of 1.06 billion
US dollars between January and May, up 21 percent on the 1997
period.
</P>
<P>
The city's processing sector continued to enjoy strong momentum
during the period, with the trade volume for the sector's 700-odd
enterprises hitting 334 million US dollars by the end of May. The
figure represented a 16 percent rise on the previous year's period
and accounted for over 40 percent of the city's total exports.
</P>
<P>
Yantai has established trade ties with 81 countries and
regions, or 19 more than in 1997. Period exports to Europe, the
United States, the Middle East and Africa reached 220 million US
dollars, up 46 percent on the 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Yantai's foreign-funded enterprises reported exports of 600
million US dollars, or 73 percent of the total. Sixteen
enterprises had exports over five million US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
Imports have also been subject to rapid growth, with imported
goods for the period growing by 62 percent to 260 million US
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
