<HEADLINE> Iran Announces Dates of Register for Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian Interior Ministry has
announced August 28 as the date to start register applicants for
the third elections of the Experts Assembly, a powerful body to
determine the country's supreme leader.
</P>
<P>
The elections became a hot topic in the country as political
factions hold different views about the procedures of the
elections.
</P>
<P>
Applicants for membership in the Experts Assembly can enroll
at the governor general's office in each province from August 28
to September 3, the morning daily Iran News Wednesday quoted a
statement from the Interior Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
The elections for the Experts Assembly will be held on October
23 to choose 86 members from the country's 28 provinces. Each of
them has one to six seats according to their population.
</P>
<P>
However, it was not announced whether the Guardians Council
would screen the qualifications of the applicants as it had done
before in other elections.
</P>
<P>
The moderate factions called for nullification of the
conservative-dominated Guardians Council to screen the
qualifications of the candidates.
</P>
<P>
Following the mid-term elections for the Majlis (Parliament)
in March, the moderates accused the conservatives of abusing the
Guardians Council's rights after a number of important moderate
candidates were rejected by the council.
</P>
<P>
Criticizing the conservatives for creating hurdles for the
government of the moderate President Mohammad Khatami, the
moderates expected to have more influence on other sensitive
bodies to pave the way for Khatami's reforms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
