<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A three-day Thai Trade Fair 1998
opened here Wednesday aiming to boost trade between Thailand and
Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Thai Deputy Foreign Minister Sukhumbhand Paribatra
inaugurated the fair, which is also aimed at exploring business
potentials and familiarizing Thai businessmen with their
Bangladeshi counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Forty-five Thai companies and 60 Thai businessmen are
participating in the 40-booth fair, the second held in the
Bangladeshi capital by Thailand. The first Thai trade fair was
held here in 1997.
</P>
<P>
During the fair, a symposium on "Trade and Investment
Opportunities in Bangladesh for Thai Businessmen" will be held.
</P>
<P>
A six-day "Thai Food Week" featuring authentic Thai cuisine is
now being held in Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
Trade between the two countries amounted to 154 million U.S.
dollars last year, much in favor of Thailand, according to a
source of the Thai Embassy here.
</P>
<P>
And it was up to the businessmen of both sides to reduce the
trade gap, the source said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand, which is undergoing economic difficulties, is looking
for new markets to boost its exports and Bangladesh could be
attractive to the country's businessmen and entrepreneurs, the
Thai Embassy source said. 
</P>
