<HEADLINE> 10 Rebels Killed in North by Sri Lankan Troops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- at least 10 Tamil rebels were
killed Tuesday in fighting in Northern Province of Sri Lanka
between rebels and government troops, according to a military
spokesman Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said the government troops observed a
group of rebels at around 4:30 p.m. Tuesday in Kilinochchi and
engaged them with mortars and artillery causing casualties among
the rebels.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan Air Force engaged the Tamil rebels who rushed to
the location to carry away their casualties.
</P>
<P>
Ground troops confirmed at least eight rebels killed and a
large number injured due to the air and artillery attacks, Dewage
said.
</P>
<P>
In another incident in northwest Kunchukklam Tuesday afternoon,
government troops also killed two terrorists, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels Tuesday morning attacked a police special task
force's "route clearing" patrol near the village of Paulukunawa in
Ampara district, Eastern Province, killing 12 troops and injuring
14 others. The rebels themselves also suffered 20 deaths.
</P>
<P>
Rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam have been
fighting a war against the government since 1983 for a separate
state in the north and east of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
