<DOCNO> XIE19980708.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-08 09:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel's Local Industrial Sales Keep </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Almost half of Israel's
industrial companies reported a serious drop in sales to the
domestic market in the second quarter of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Local daily Haaretz Wednesday quoted a survey of the
Manufacturers' Association of Israel as showing that 45 percent of
industrial companies suffered a slowdown in domestic sales while
only 24 percent reported higher sales.
</P>
<P>
The drop followed the trend in the first quarter this year, in
which 53 percent of the companies reported a drop in sales.
</P>
<P>
The survey also shows that the textiles and clothing sectors
reported the worst performance in the second quarter, with sales
declining by about 70 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 41 percent of the firms reported low profits in this
period while only 8 percent listed better profits.
</P>
<P>
Industrial production also fell in the second quarter with 38
percent of the plants reporting cutbacks in production.
</P>
<P>
Israel's economy has been slowing down in the past two years
since the Likud government took a tight economic policy in a bid
to cut the high inflation rate.
</P>
<P>
According to a forecast of Israeli Finance Ministry, the
economic growth of Israel in 1998 would be only between one to two
percent, the lowest growth rate in decade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980708.0190 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Businesses Boom in Hebei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 8 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
ranks second in China with 2.15 million private industrial
and commercial households and 6.3 million employees.
</P>
<P>
The province ranks third in terms of registered capital for
related businesses.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises under private ownership had a 1997 output value
of 64.2 billion yuan, business turnover over 73.4 billion yuan,
and retail sales volume of 21.1 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Some 15,897 private companies in the province have registered
capital of over one million yuan each, with 1,200 reporting
capital of over five million yuan each. The number of private
group companies, a sector which emerged in the 1980s, has soared
to 308.
</P>
<P>
Some 520 private companies have purchased, leased or merged 370
small to medium-sized bankrupt or inefficient state-owned
enterprises. Over 2,100 private companies produce parts and
components for local state businesses.
</P>
<P>
The private sector has absorbed 280,000 laid-off and surplus
workers from local state-owned and collective businesses, or 45
percent of the local total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
