<HEADLINE> German Tourist Killed, 15 Injured in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A German tourist has been killed and
15 others injured in a traffic accident in eastern Egypt, the
Middle East News Agency reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Security sources said the incident occurred on Tuesday when a
micro-bus carrying the tourists collided with a truck on the
highway from Hurghada, about 560 kilometers southeast of Cairo,
down to Safaga.
</P>
<P>
Both Hurghada and Safaga are Egypt's Red Sea resorts.
</P>
<P>
The wounded are six Germans, four Italians, three Egyptians and
two Belgians, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
A woman was flown to the capital for treatment and the others
were rushed to hospitals in Hurghada and Safaga, the news agency
quoted the sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The micro-bus was rented by a tourist company, the sources
said, adding that the police are investigating the incident.
</P>
</TEXT>
