<HEADLINE> Zhongyuan Oilfield Improves Efficiency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Zhongyuan Oilfield, one of the
leading oil producers in China, pumped two million tons of crude
oil in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
The output accounted for half of the oilfield's annual
production quota, according to an official in the oilfield.
</P>
<P>
Comprehensive measures such as pumping water into wells enabled
Zhongyuan to raise its daily average output to 11,049 tons in the
first half year, some 90 tons more than the targeted figure.
</P>
<P>
The field has also adopted other measures to cut
production cost and improve efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The measures are expected to increase per-well output by 1,000
tons annually. 
</P>
