<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, July 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV -- Ukraine's Supreme Soviet, or parliament, Tuesday ended
a nearly two-month deadlock in finding a new head by electing
Alexandr Tkachenko as its speaker.
</P>
<P>
Tkachenko, 59, of the Peasants Party, finally won a 232-37 vote
after the unicameral legislative body had held over 20 rounds of
failed voting since May 12. Forty-five votes were declared
invalid. (Ukraine-New Parliament Speaker)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov on Tuesday
called for continued Russian-U.S. joint efforts to seek a
political solution to the Kosovo problem.
</P>
<P>
Primakov told the Itar-Tass news agency that joint moves by
Russia and the United States were of special importance prior to
the six-nation Contact Group's discussions on the Kosovo crisis in
Bonn, which is scheduled to start Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Together with U.S. envoy Richard Holbrooke, Russian Deputy
Foreign Minister Nikolai Afanasyevsky visited Kosovo on Sunday and
held talks with Ibrahim Rugova, a Kosovo ethnic Albanian
leader. It was the first joint action taken by the two envoys over
the crisis. (Russia-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
