<P>
WASHINGTON -- Closer military-to-military contacts between the
United States and China are "coming on line," said White House
Spokesman Michael McCurry on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The development, McCurry told a press briefing here, is part of
the efforts to establish U.S.-China strategic partnership.
</P>
<P>
McCurry said the two countries have agreed to hold the first
annual meeting of the Military Maritime Consultative Agreement
Forum later this month, so as to promote safety in naval and air
operations and avoid incidents at sea. (US-China-Military
Contacts)
</P>
<P>
