<P>
BONN -- The two most important European stock exchanges, the
London Stock Exchange and Frankfurt's Deutsche Boerse, have agreed
to form a strategic alliance, aiming to create a pan-European
stock market.
</P>
<P>
As announced in a joint statement issued in London Tuesday,
the two exchanges have agreed, as the first step, to establish a
joint venture with equal holdings. (Germany-Britain-Stock
