</P>
<P>
WARSAW -- Antarctica experienced a warm winter with showers,
instead of the usual snowfalls, in its coldest month of June this
year, a Polish scientist said.
</P>
<P>
Professor S.R-Suszczewski, a researcher in the biological
institute of the Polish Academy of Sciences, said this winter in
Antarctica was the warmest since 1977, the Polish Press Agency
reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Polish observation station in Antarctica measured a record
high of 9 degrees above zero centigrade in June, the scientist
said. (Antarctica-Warm Winter) 
