<HEADLINE> Advanced Heat Pump Set for Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A recent agreement signed in Dalian
calls for China and Japan to join hands in developing an
advanced heat pump which uses new technology and
refrigerants.
</P>
<P>
The pump will be developed by the Dalian Sanyo Refrigeration Co
Ltd, Dalian University of Science and Engineering and Sanyo
Electric Co Ltd of Japan.
</P>
<P>
The heat pump will use lithium bromide as a replacement for
freon and will provide both heating and cooling functions.
</P>
<P>
The new equipment will reduce environmental pollution, improve
the quality of refrigeration equipment and raise efficiency. The
pump will also accelerate the development of worldwide
refrigeration industry, according to Xiao Yongqin, general manager
of Dalian Sanyo Refrigeration Company Limited.
</P>
<P>
The tripartite agreement calls for Chinese and Japanese
engineers to develop at least five advanced technical
innovations by the year 2000. 
