<DOCNO> XIE19980708.0221 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Registered U.S. Vehicles Top 200 Million by June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The number of registered
vehicles in the United States has surpassed 200 million for the
first time, according to a study released Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Polk Co., which produced the study from state registration
records, said there have been more than 201 million cars and
trucks registered in the country by the end of June.
</P>
<P>
"Thirty years after the country's human population surpassed
200 million, the number of vehicles in operation has done the
same," said Glenn Forbes, vice president of Polk.
</P>
<P>
The study also showed the popularity of light trucks -- sport
utility vehicles, pickups, vans and mini-vans.
</P>
<P>
During the past decade, the number of cars on the road has
risen 4.82 million, compared with a rise of 29.05 million for
trucks, said the annual Polk study.
</P>
<P>
However, in November 1997, the number of new light trucks
registered actually exceeded the number of new cars for the first
time, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
