<HEADLINE> Hebei Development Zone Witnesses Rapid Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Langfang Economic and
Technological Development Zone in north China's Hebei Province
generated an industrial output value of 512 million yuan during
the first half of this year, up 63.4 percent on the 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
The zone, located between Beijing and the coastal city of
Tianjin, achieved an export volume of 18.92 million US dollars for
the period, up 98 percent.
</P>
<P>
The zone was established in June, 1992, and currently has 515
registered enterprises, including 161 operational firms. The zone
has 50 operational and 34 foreign-funded projects under
construction.
</P>
<P>
The Langfang zone has attracted investments from 16 countries
and regions and plans to attract additional funds from the
world's top 500 companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
