<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Muslim Restaurants Open Nationwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- China has a total of 120,000
Muslim restaurants nationwide and Muslim food has emerged as the
most popular ethnic food for the nation's 55 minority
nationalities.
</P>
<P>
Ma Yunfu, deputy director of the Islamic Association of China,
told participants at the recent First National Symposium on Muslim
Food Culture that most Muslim restaurants in China's 30 provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions are under private ownership.
</P>
<P>
He said the popularity of Muslim restaurants indicates that the
custom and traditions of China's minority groups are fully
respected. He noted that the Muslim catering trade has witnessed
rapid development, especially in northern and northwestern China
which are home to Muslims living in compact communities.
</P>
<P>
Muslim enterprises account for 80 percent of the total number
of restaurants in northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region, or "China's Muslim Province".
</P>
<P>
The number of Muslim restaurants in neighboring Shaanxi
Province has skyrocketed from 640 in 1990 to some 5,000
today, or 27 percent of the total number of enterprises in the
province's catering sector.
</P>
<P>
China's Muslim catering trade has a history of over 1,300 years
and the nation now has a Muslim population of around 20 million
people.
</P>
<P>
The Xinjiang Uygur and Ningxia Hui autonomous regions, as well
as a number of provinces, have adopted local regulations to
protect the Muslim food industry and catering sector.
</P>
<P>
The China Cuisine Association established a Muslim division in
1996 to list and reintroduce traditional Muslim dishes and snack
foods. The association has since compiled a publication listing
nearly 2,000 Muslim dishes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
