<HEADLINE> Frankfurt, London Stock Exchanges Form Alliance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The two most important European stock
exchanges, the London Stock Exchange and Frankfurt's Deutsche
Boerse, have agreed to form a strategic alliance, aiming to create
a pan-European stock market.
</P>
<P>
As announced in a joint statement issued in London Tuesday,
the two exchanges have agreed, as the first step, to establish a
joint venture with equal holdings.
</P>
<P>
They also have said the alliance would be open to other stock
exchanges, with the ultimate goal to create a single European
stock market based on a common electronic trading platform.
</P>
</TEXT>
