<HEADLINE> Thai Deputy Foreign Minister Arrives in Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Thai Deputy Foreign Minister
Sukhumbhand Paribatra arrived here Wednesday on a three-day visit
to explore investment facilities in Bangladesh for his country's
businessmen, the Thai Embassy said.
</P>
<P>
The Thai deputy foreign minister will hold talks with
Bangladeshi State Minister for Foreign Affairs Abu Hasan Chowdhury
on bilateral relations and regional and international issues of
mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina and Foreign Minister
Abdus Samad Azad will also meet the Thai guest separately.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Paribatra will address a seminar on "Investment
Opportunities for Thai Businessmen" and attend a Thai trade fair
to be held here.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on avoidance of double taxation is expected to be
signed between the two countries during the visit by the Thai
deputy foreign minister.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, an extradition treaty is also expected to
be signed between Dhaka and Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
The treaty, the first the Bangladeshi government signs with a
foreign country, aims to bring back Major Bazlul Huda, one of the
accused in the murder case of Sheikh Mujib -- Bangladesh's first
prime minister after independence in 1971 who was assassinated in
1975. Huda has been detained in a Thai jail. 
</P>
