<HEADLINE> Tajikistan, Belarus Call CIS Acceptable Transition Format </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Tajikistan and Belarus said Tuesday
the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) is an acceptable
format for cooperation among former Soviet republics in a
transition period.
</P>
<P>
In a joint communique released before Belarussian Foreign
Minister Ivan Antonovich ended his two-day stay in Dushanbe,
Tajikistan, he and his Tajik counterpart Talbak Nazarov called for
speeding up the CIS integration.
</P>
<P>
As quoted by an Interfax news agency report reaching here, they
also vowed to further improve the CIS mechanism that has been
grouping the 12 countries, including Russia, together since the
disintegration of the Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with Antonovich, Belarussian President Emomali
Rakhmonov said reform is a must for the CIS, and every member
state of the grouping should live up to its commitments under
multinational treaties.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral issues, Rakhmonov called for expanding trade ties
between Tajikistan and Belarus, and speeding up the preparation
for a bilateral friendship and cooperation treaty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
