<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka, Malaysia to Set Up Furniture Joint Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A Sri Lankan-Malaysian joint
venture will be set up to export pine wood furniture, State Timber
Corporation (STC) said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The STC said it will hold a 51-percent stake in the venture and
will provide the necessary wood, while Malaysia will offer the
technological aspects.
</P>
<P>
There has been worldwide demand for Sri Lanka's pine furniture.
The STC received more than 600,000 orders during an exhibition
held here earlier this year, the STC said.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka already has two factories producing quality furniture
but further technical assistance is needed to meet large numbers
of orders.
</P>
<P>
In Sri Lanka, there are over 16,000 hectares of pine
cultivation which ensure a ready supply of wood for furniture
production, the STC said. 
</P>
