<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Argentine government will
issue a seven-year term bond in German marks equivalent to 413.5
million U.S. dollars repayable in full upon maturity.
</P>
<P>
According to an Economics Ministry press release issued here
Tuesday, the issue of the bond will start on July 29, and it will
be issued mainly by Bayerische Landesbank.
</P>
<P>
The bond will be issued with a re-offering price of 99.14
percent with the annual interest rate standing at 7.875 percent.
</P>
<P>
The issue is framed within budget authorizations approved by
National Congress and will serve for compensating financing needs
of the government in the third quarter, the press release said.
