<HEADLINE> China to Launch More Securities Investment Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- China has announced its resolve to
launch an additional five securities investment funds by the end
of this year.
</P>
<P>
The final fund in the first group of funds will be launched in
the near future, according to the China Securities Regulatory
Commission (CSRC), the country's securities watchdog.
</P>
<P>
Securities investment funds represent an important channel for
fostering institutional investors and are conducive to the
long-term stability and development of the Chinese securities
market, according to a CSRC spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman noted that "the introduction of funds to China's
securities market early this year has helped enliven the market,
improve investment sentiment and enable investors to make rational
choices."
</P>
<P>
The plan to Launch more funds indicates the the strong
determination of the authorities to develop the securities market
and also caters to the need of investors.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his confidence that listing more securities
investment funds will breathe new life into the expanding market.
</P>
<P>
Four funds are currently listed on the nation's stock exchanges
-- the Jintai, Kaiyuan, Xinghua and Anxin funds. The closed-end
funds are currently valued at two billion yuan (240 million
US dollars) each.  
</P>
