<HEADLINE> Brazil's Car Production Falls in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Car production
totalled 876,958 units in the first six months of 1998, a 14
percent reduction from the same period last year when about 1.03
million cars were produced.
</P>
<P>
The National Association of Auto Manufacturers said the sales
of cars on the domestic market dropped by 23.36 percent to 647,000
units in this period, compared with the first half of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Jose Carlos Pinheiro Neto, chairman of the association, said
the goal of two million cars was hard to fulfill this year, and
only 1.75 million cars were expected to be produced, a 15 percent
drop over last year.
</P>
<P>
Although production was down, the export of cars increased 10
percent, to 210,000 units, in the first six months of 1998, the
association said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
