<HEADLINE> Experts Call for More New Building Materials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese experts have called for
increased production of new building materials in order to improve
the level of the country's thriving construction sector.
</P>
<P>
Today's edition of People's Daily reported that China
initiated the development of new building materials in 1979, but
is nonetheless far behind developed countries in the use of
related products.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the output value for new building
materials accounts for a mere 15 percent of the gross value for
related products.
</P>
<P>
For example, new waterproof materials are being used only in a
five percent of construction projects, compared to a usage rate of
between 75-90 percent in some foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
New insulation materials are used in 10 percent of projects,
with the usage rate for wallboard standing at 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
Experts point out that the increased use of new wallboard and
materials will help the nation conserve arable land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
