<HEADLINE> Annan Shocked Over Death of Detained Nigerian Politician </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan said Tuesday that he was shocked by the news of the sudden
death of Nigeria's detained politician Moshood Abiola.
</P>
<P>
An official statement from Nigeria's presidency said Abiola,
detained since 1994 when he declared himself president, died of
apparent heart attack Tuesday during a meeting with Nigerian
officials and members of a visiting U.S. delegation.
</P>
<P>
"The Nigerian government has confirmed to me this afternoon the
death today of Moshood Abiola," said Annan.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief said he had expected Abiola's imminent release,
along with other detainees, and the beginning of a process to
restore democratic civilian rule to Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
"My heart goes out to his family. I wish to express to them my
sincerest condolence," Annan said.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that the Government of Nigeria would make good on its
pledge to release all remaining political prisoners
unconditionally and to define a credible process for the
democratic transition to civilian rule within a reasonable time
frame," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
