<HEADLINE> Croatia's Suker Lauds Coach Blazevic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Croatian striker Davor Suker has sung
praises for his coach Miroslav Blazevic.
</P>
<P>
"Throughout his career, Blazevic has proven his exceptional talent.
With all his achievements, he has succeeded in bringing the players,
the fans, and the media together," said Suker on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He added: "Because of his psychological approach to the game, he
has been able to be flexible with us thoughout our 50-day stay here.
He's been everything but a dictator."
</P>
<P>
Suker said France may have sapped their energy after playing two of
their games into extra time.
</P>
<P>
"I think we have an advantage over France because two of their
matches have gone into extra time and so they've spent more energy...
We have 50-50 chance of winning the game," he said.
</P>
<P>
Sukor said he has got tips from teammate Zvonimir Boban on Marcel
Desailly if the French defender marks him in Wednesday's semifinal.
</P>
<P>
Boban and Desailly are playing together in the Italian club side AC
Milan.
</P>
<P>
He said: "I am not concentrating on being the top scorer, my
objective is to play in the final.
</P>
<P>
"Asking me if I am happy to be in the semifinals is a dumb question
-- a player at this level is not happy just participating. He's here
to win." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
