<HEADLINE> Brazil Beat Netherlands after Penalty Shoot-out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MARSEILLE, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Brazil beat the Netherlands after
penalty shoot-out to advance into the final of the France'98.
</P>
<P>
The two teams played to a 1-1 tie after 90 minutes and failed to
score a golden goal in the extra time.
</P>
<P>
In the penalty shoot-out, the Brazilian players hit in all their
first four goals while their goal-keeper Taffarel saved two shots
from the Dutch team to give Brazil the 5-3 victory. 
</P>
